    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available is a 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2) featuring the 3.6L M96 flat-six engine equipped with VarioCam Plus. This naturally aspirated powerplant is mated to a 6-speed Getrag manual transaxle, ensuring a direct mechanical connection. The IMS bearing has been proactively upgraded to a ceramic dual-row solution, and the Rear Main Seal is verified dry. The chassis dynamics are maintained by a factory-spec multi-link rear suspension and MacPherson front struts, providing the communicative steering rack feedback these cars are known for. While the exterior shows light patina consistent with a well-loved driver, the mechanical vitals are excellent, with a recent oil analysis showing no debris and a clean borescope of the cylinder walls. This is a high-revving, rear-engine icon ready for the apex.",
